snippet: HealthCare.gov, the federal website, was temporarily overwhelmed by a rush to sign up, but officials said they were confident that they would reach their enrollment goal.
abstract: Frenzied last-minute scramble to sign up for health insurance overloads phone lines and temporarily overwhelms federal website HealthCare.gov; comes as hundreds of thousands of people around country race to beat deadline to obtain coverage under Affordable Care Act; officials say they are confident they will reach their enrollment goal of seven million.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Jess Bidgood from Somersworth, N.H., Lisa Maria Garza from Dallas, Anemona Hartocollis from New York, Nick Madigan from Miami, Colin Miner from Portland, Ore., and Michael D. Shear from Washington.

lead_paragraph: HealthCare.gov, the federal website, was temporarily overwhelmed by a rush to sign up, but officials said they were confident that they would reach their enrollment goal.

headline.main: Health Care Signups Reach Frenzy in Final Day to Enroll
